This paper discusses plagiarism detection techniques using machine learning, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), making cs.CL and cs.IR the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of various tools and systems for plagiarism detection, which could fall under the category of cyber security (cs.CR) or cryptography and security (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the taxonomy of various forms of plagiarism, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves classification and categorization.
